01:23:43,055 --> 01:23:43,335
[SPEAKER_07]: I think

816
01:23:44,544 --> 01:23:57,888
[SPEAKER_07]: we can set a relatively clear principle and line in saying that properties that are owned by the trustees of Tufts College should generally be considered for some sort of institutional zoning.

817
01:23:57,928 --> 01:24:09,972
[SPEAKER_07]: Now, whether that's a campus type district or potentially some sort of mixed use district with specific kind of Tufts oriented requirements, I think that that addresses the edge issues.

818
01:24:11,372 --> 01:24:13,033
[SPEAKER_07]: But I do think we should think about the

819
01:24:15,220 --> 01:24:22,525
[SPEAKER_07]: privately owned, mostly not by the shell company that I can never think of the name of.

820
01:24:22,545 --> 01:24:24,066
[SPEAKER_08]: Walnut Hill, I think.

821
01:24:24,946 --> 01:24:26,227
[SPEAKER_07]: Walnut Hill, that sounds right.

822
01:24:27,248 --> 01:24:30,850
[SPEAKER_07]: But, you know, still a private, privately owned, even though affiliated with Tufts.

823
01:24:31,411 --> 01:24:37,515
[SPEAKER_07]: I do think like there's clarity for the public in setting a clear line between those two things.

824
01:24:39,336 --> 01:24:41,797
[SPEAKER_07]: And I think actually the boundaries we have are pretty close on that.

825
01:24:41,857 --> 01:24:42,598
[SPEAKER_07]: And I don't think that

826
01:24:43,340 --> 01:24:53,666
[SPEAKER_07]: means we can't have the conversation about what mixed use looks like in the edge cases where those properties may be owned by Tufts formally.

827
01:24:55,147 --> 01:25:07,455
[SPEAKER_07]: But I do think it helps to clarify the process because I think there's going to be, even in those edge cases, specific things that we're going to want to put in place since the ownership and development potential is still

828
01:25:08,483 --> 01:25:10,044
[SPEAKER_07]: different given the Dover amendment.

829
01:25:10,124 --> 01:25:13,247
[SPEAKER_07]: So that's, I actually think we're really close to having a clear line.

830
01:25:13,767 --> 01:25:26,636
[SPEAKER_07]: My preference would be let's include the Think Clemens property, but not the Tufts owned property on that, on that, on those two sides of Boston Ave, north of Harvard Street.

831
01:25:27,437 --> 01:25:35,743
[SPEAKER_07]: Because I think that just helps us to have the right conversations about the Boston Avenue zoning and about the Tufts institutional zoning options.

