840
01:26:09,978 --> 01:26:13,319
[SPEAKER_08]: I hope that we are thinking of the future here.

841
01:26:13,339 --> 01:26:23,603
[SPEAKER_08]: I see Boston Avenue with its two new green line stops as being one of the probably most rapidly changing parts of our city, if not now, very soon.

842
01:26:24,784 --> 01:26:27,945
[SPEAKER_08]: And while I understand the kind of

843
01:26:28,434 --> 01:26:38,761
[SPEAKER_08]: nuance and carefulness around whether predominantly residential properties should be included in this zone or not.

844
01:26:38,781 --> 01:26:44,225
[SPEAKER_08]: 10, 15, 20 years from now, that may be less defined.

845
01:26:44,486 --> 01:26:49,349
[SPEAKER_08]: And I think we should be encouraging mixed use across the entirety of the corridor.

846
01:26:49,449 --> 01:26:57,555
[SPEAKER_08]: I would advocate for a more cohesive and unified zoning approach to this corridor rather than a piecemeal approach to it.

847
01:26:58,497 --> 01:27:08,483
[SPEAKER_08]: Um, it's really difficult for me to see one property, um, next to another that are zoned very differently, and it almost pits properties against each other.

848
01:27:08,503 --> 01:27:27,213
[SPEAKER_08]: Um, I also, uh, agree with Alicia that it's really hard to think of these, um, these boundaries as separate, because as you have pushed on one this evening, you've pulled on another, and, um, I will admit, I appreciate, Matt, that you've acknowledged it, but, uh,

849
01:27:27,969 --> 01:27:34,074
[SPEAKER_08]: Disappointing to come to another meeting that was billed as Boston Avenue and Tufts and really only focus on Boston Avenue.

850
01:27:34,935 --> 01:27:39,738
[SPEAKER_08]: You educated me last time that the advertisement was for Boston Avenue only, not Tufts.

851
01:27:39,999 --> 01:27:41,019
[SPEAKER_08]: Tonight that was different.

852
01:27:41,900 --> 01:27:56,732
[SPEAKER_08]: We need to be talking about these in conjunction with each other because while we might have a line in how we treat them, the way that they function and the way that people experience them and the way they contribute to our city are very much co-joined.

853
01:27:59,594 --> 01:28:07,578
[SPEAKER_08]: I also agree with the notion that this corridor should be treated differently than other corridors because it is different than other corridors.

854
01:28:07,618 --> 01:28:11,040
[SPEAKER_08]: It has different pressures than other corridors, other squares.

855
01:28:11,941 --> 01:28:15,763
[SPEAKER_08]: And so making sure we're responsive to what this place needs is important.

