[SPEAKER_08]: We just want to have an opportunity to see what's out there, but I understand where you are in the process and certainly the complexity of it.

922
01:37:04,187 --> 01:37:15,892
[SPEAKER_08]: I did have one other question for Alicia and some of the points she was making earlier about the church and about Tufts-owned buildings or institutionally-owned buildings, whether that's a religious use or a

923
01:37:16,861 --> 01:37:17,661
[SPEAKER_08]: educational use.

924
01:37:17,781 --> 01:37:29,166
[SPEAKER_08]: Alicia, you mentioned a scenario where something could be developed as a religious use or an institutional use by that nonprofit owner, and it would be subject to Dover.

925
01:37:29,206 --> 01:37:31,186
[SPEAKER_08]: You described a scenario where

926
01:37:33,893 --> 01:37:39,857
[SPEAKER_08]: those properties could be sold to a developer and then they would be subject to the standard site plan review.

927
01:37:41,238 --> 01:37:51,984
[SPEAKER_08]: Is there also a scenario where that property is leased by a nonprofit institution to a developer?

928
01:37:53,105 --> 01:37:56,427
[SPEAKER_08]: And what is the applicability of Dover in that situation?

929
01:37:57,027 --> 01:37:57,348
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you.

930
01:37:59,109 --> 01:37:59,589
[SPEAKER_08]: Director Hunt.

931
01:38:00,502 --> 01:38:12,087
[SPEAKER_05]: Chair, and I may, let me comment on this and I may actually refer this to our graduate student Christian who literally defended his thesis today on Dover at Tufts UEP.

932
01:38:13,987 --> 01:38:22,551
[SPEAKER_05]: If the building is used for educational purposes and designed and used for educational purposes,

933
01:38:23,184 --> 01:38:34,859
[SPEAKER_05]: then it's subject to Dover, if it is used for non educational purposes and I believe it says regardless of who owns it, then it's so.

934
01:38:35,633 --> 01:38:41,995
[SPEAKER_05]: You know what, Christian do you want to speak to it because you can actually I think you're going to be way more coherent than I am off the cuff on this.

935
01:38:42,715 --> 01:38:43,215
[SPEAKER_05]: You don't mind.

936
01:38:43,735 --> 01:38:44,215
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah.

937
01:38:44,495 --> 01:38:55,658
[SPEAKER_00]: So, under the law, the court requires that a educational or religious institution must serve an edge like educationally significant or religious goal.

938
01:38:56,598 --> 01:38:59,901
[SPEAKER_00]: and be the dominant purpose of the use.

939
01:39:00,342 --> 01:39:13,974
[SPEAKER_00]: So if a religious institution like the church were to lease that land, if it's not a predominant use that supports a religious mission or educationally significant goal, it would not qualify for Dover protections under the law.

940
01:39:14,654 --> 01:39:23,302
[SPEAKER_00]: So if it was a primarily residential building, it would not receive Dover protections and have to go through the standard process regardless of it being owned by a religious institution.

941
01:39:27,611 --> 01:39:54,488
[SPEAKER_05]: And I think the big clarification, right, because there was this question came up with the Tufts dorm, because it was being developed by a private developer, but it was on land owned by Tufts, and it was being used by Tufts for Tufts housing, and only Tufts students, enrolled students may live there, which is why it serves the educational purpose, as opposed to if it was leased to a private developer and leased out

942
01:39:55,345 --> 01:39:59,929
[SPEAKER_05]: the units leased to the general public, then it would stop being a Dover use.

943
01:40:02,312 --> 01:40:03,172
[SPEAKER_10]: Council President Behrs.

944
01:40:04,193 --> 01:40:10,619
[SPEAKER_07]: I think just to further clarify on Christian's example and congratulations on defending your thesis and then coming to this meeting.

945
01:40:14,402 --> 01:40:21,409
[SPEAKER_07]: It sounds like to go a step further, if the church was leasing a residential property

946
01:40:22,403 --> 01:40:30,626
[SPEAKER_07]: you know, let's say they lease something, they built homes on it, and those were leased to the public, as Alicia said, for rent, that would not qualify, that would not be tax exempt.

947
01:40:31,066 --> 01:40:39,269
[SPEAKER_07]: If they were built, you know, using that for housing of clergy members or of the church for the religious purpose, then that would continue to be Dover exempt.

948
01:40:39,409 --> 01:40:43,371
[SPEAKER_07]: Similarly, so you slot an educational institution in there.

949
01:40:44,031 --> 01:40:49,193
[SPEAKER_07]: If Tufts wants to rent to the public, that's not exempt, but if they want to house their own students, then that is.

950
01:40:51,354 --> 01:40:52,094
[SPEAKER_07]: I'm seeing nods.

951
01:40:53,535 --> 01:40:53,855
[SPEAKER_02]: All right.

952
01:40:55,075 --> 01:40:55,635
[SPEAKER_02]: That's correct.

953
01:40:58,856 --> 01:40:59,196
[SPEAKER_10]: All right.

954
01:40:59,496 --> 01:41:00,156
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

955
